{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"27b15991-beba-49f6-9453-482e06f60f67","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the VSTest compatibility layer (`vstest.console`) is disabled by default.** The SDK now exclusively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the test runner.\n\nThis means `vstest.console.exe`, `dotnet test` (in its legacy VSTest mode), and any CI step that relies on the VSTest adapter protocol will no longer discover or run tests.\n\n### Fix options\n\n**Option A** – Re-enable VSTest support by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n  <!-- This is the key property -->\n  <TestingPlatformEnableVSTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformEnableVSTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Option B (recommended)** – Migrate your CI pipeline away from `vstest.console` to the new runner:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test          # works natively with Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8+\n# or run the test exe directly:\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --list-tests\n```\n\nWith `dotnet test` on recent SDK versions, the platform is auto-detected and no adapter is needed.\n\nWould you like me to update your project file or help migrate a CI pipeline step?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"46c3fd53-e72d-4953-bc9e-903d5c17f715","outputTokens":328,"requestId":"BC27:A067E:209089D:247D87E:69FAABD9"},"id":"29f6e974-45c7-46ab-9284-23fca34c76a9","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:48:02.669Z","parentId":"f4a8c745-5de5-41d4-a626-1d67c72645b7"}
